# graphify

Knowledge graph lives at `graphify-out/`. Binary: `/home/billy/.local/bin/graphify` (uv tool `graphifyy`).

## Before Architecture Questions

1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for community hubs and god nodes.
2. If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, use the wiki instead of raw file scans.

## Cross-Module Queries

Prefer graph traversal over grep for "how does X relate to Y?":

```bash
/home/billy/.local/bin/graphify query "<question>"
/home/billy/.local/bin/graphify path "<concept A>" "<concept B>"
/home/billy/.local/bin/graphify explain "<concept>"
```

## Keep Graph Fresh

After modifying code in a session:

```bash
cd /opt/butterflyguy && /home/billy/.local/bin/graphify update .
```

AST-only, no API cost. Compare `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` commit hash to `git rev-parse HEAD` to detect staleness.
